HEADWORD: Chesses
<hw>Chess"es</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>chassis</ets> a framework of carpenty.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>The platforms, consisting of two or more planks doweled together,
for the flooring of a temporary military bridge.</def>
<rj><au>Wilhelm.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧A singular, <xex>chess</xex>, is sometimes used.
⟦ldquo⟧Each <xex>chess</xex> consists of three planks.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Farrow.</au></rj></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chessil</ent>⟦br⟧
